     3	## Purpose
     4	Define the security posture for Minakeep's current shipped slice.
     5	
     6	## Core Security Rules
     7	- keep `/app` routes private to the owner account
     8	- expose only explicitly published notes and explicitly published links on public routes
     9	- do not log secrets, passwords, session tokens, or full private note/link payloads
    10	- validate owner credentials on the server only
    11	- store only the owner password hash in SQLite
    12	- accept saved-link URLs only for `http` and `https`
    13	- keep AI provider tokens and base URLs server-only
    14	- do not send private note or link content to unconfigured or fallback endpoints silently
    15	- visible AI failure copy may name missing env keys, but it must never echo configured secret values
    16	
    17	## Secrets and Config
    18	- keep `AUTH_SECRET`, `DATABASE_URL`, `OWNER_USERNAME`, and `OWNER_PASSWORD` in environment configuration only
    19	- keep `LLM_BASE`, `TOKEN`, and `MODEL` in shell or local environment only
    20	- never commit seeded credentials or secret values
